President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Sandra L. Thompson as the Director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA). The FHFA oversees Fannie Mae, Freddie Mac, and the Federal Home Loan Bank System, and is responsible for the $7.2 trillion mortgage finance market. Thompson has over four decades of government experience in financial regulation, risk management, and consumer protection. She has been serving as the Acting Director of FHFA since earlier this year. Prior to joining FHFA, Thompson worked at the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) for more than 23 years, where she held various leadership positions, including Director of the Division of Risk Management Supervision. Thompson's nomination is subject to Senate confirmation. She is a native of Chicago, a graduate of Howard University, and has two adult sons.